We present a computational study of low-energy Ir4+ crystal field excitation spectra in Sr3NiIrO6 using resonant inelastic x-ray scattering (RIXS) spectroscopy at the Ir4+ L3 absorption edge. The results are compared to an experiment performed at the beamline ID20 of the European Synchrotron Radiation Facility[1]
